

     
      i went to the dentist to see about a filling that fell out.  he'd done a root canal and filled the hole as a temporary solution while the thing healed enough to do a crown.  sound idea.  i thought.  then the filling fell out as i was eating.  and the hole left over got annoying as food kept getting stuck up there.  then it started to hurt.  turns out the entire tooth split and there was no saving it.  right in the side of my smile.  thanks.  so now i have this big-ass hole there.  and the sweet part?  it'll cost me $5000 to fill it properly.  thank you dentist guy.  moral of the story?  find a good dentist.  spoil the shit out of him.  be happy.  i did say GOOD dentist didn't i?
     
    
